Substitute
$x=2\cos^2t$

\begin{align}
&\int_{0}^{2}\frac{\tan^{-1}\left(\frac{2}{x}-1\right)}{\sqrt{2x-x^2}}\ dx\\
=&\ 2\int_0^{\pi/2} \tan^{-1}(\tan^2t)\overset{t\to\frac\pi2-t}{dt
= }2\int_0^{\pi/2} \cot^{-1}(\tan^2t){dt}\\
=&\ \int_0^{\pi/2} \tan^{-1}(\tan^2t)+ \cot^{-1}(\tan^2t)\ {dt}
= \int_0^{\pi/2}\frac\pi2 \ dt=\frac{\pi^2}4
\end{align}

